de.oaam.model.oaam.library

Interface DeviceTypeDissimilarity

  • All Superinterfaces:
    org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier, OaamBaseElementA
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DeviceTypeDissimilarityImpl

    public interface DeviceTypeDissimilarity
extends OaamBaseElementA
    A representation of the model object 'Device Type Dissimilarity'. Device types are declared dissimilar to all other device types in the same dissimilarity group up to a certain factor. If more accurate dissimilarity modeling is required resource type dissimilarities can be used.

    The following features are supported:

    • Devices
    • Percentage Of Common Hardware
    See Also:
    LibraryPackage.getDeviceTypeDissimilarity()

      • getPercentageOfCommonHardware

        double getPercentageOfCommonHardware()
        Returns the value of the 'Percentage Of Common Hardware' attribute. Gives an approximation of the percentage of hardware that is identical to the other devices referenced as dissimilar. By default 100% dissimilarity is assumed. Additional checks for dissimilarity are carried out with the resource types, which must also be dissimilar.
        Returns:
        the value of the 'Percentage Of Common Hardware' attribute.
        See Also:
        setPercentageOfCommonHardware(double), LibraryPackage.getDeviceTypeDissimilarity_PercentageOfCommonHardware()
